<section class="details">
   <!--Row with two columns divided in 1:2 ratio-->
   <div class="container "> 
    <div class="row ">
      <div class="col-sm-4"><img src="/assets/diet_receipe4.png" height="300" width="320"></div>
        
        <div class="col-sm-4 no-margin"> <p class="title_info">INFORMATIONS ABOUT YOUR DISH :</p>
            <div class="row details no-margin">
                <div class="col-xs-12 no-margin"> <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-time"></span> 15 mins<br><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-stats"></span> calories: 176kcal. fat: 11g. carbohydrates: 19g. protein: 2g.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="row details no-margin">
                <div class="col-xs-12 no-margin", style="text-align: justify;">These vegan popsicles swirl layers of lime-spiked coconut milk with a concentrated blackberry purée. Chia seeds are stirred into the mixture to thicken it and add texture—plus give you a healthy hit of fiber and protein.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="row details no-margin">
                <div class="col-xs-12 no-margin", style="text-align: justify;">
                  1. 1 3.5-oz. can low-fat coconut milk <br>
                  2. ¼ cup lime juice <br>
                  3. 4 tbs. light agave nectar, divided<br>
                  4. 2 tbs. black chia seeds <br>
                  5. 2 ⅓ cups (about 10 oz.) blackberries<br>
                
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row details no-margin">
                <div class="col-xs-12 no-margin" style="text-align: justify;">
                  <b>Direction</b><br>
                  1. Blend coconut milk, lime juice, 3 tbs. agave nectar, and pinch of salt, if desired, in blender until creamy. <br>
                  2. Pour all but 1⁄2 cup coconut-milk mixture into bowl, and set aside. Stir chia seeds into mixture in bowl.<br>
                  3. Add blackberries and remaining agave nectar to remaining 1⁄2 cup coconut-milk mixture in blender. Blend 1 minute, or until mostly smooth.<br>
                  4. Strain blackberry mixture through a fine-mesh strainer into a bowl or liquid measuring cup, pressing and stirring with spatula to help the liquid through. Discard seeds. (You will have about 10 oz. of liquid.)<br>
                  5. Spoon or pour 1 tbs. chia mixture into bottoms of six 3-oz. popsicle molds.<br>
                  6. Add 1 heaping tbs. berry mixture atop each. Continue layering popsicles with 1 heaping tbs. of each mixture until mixture reaches fill lines. <br>
                  7. Swirl mixtures inside molds with skewer or butter knife. <br>
                  8. Freeze 5 hours, or overnight. Run each popsicle mold under warm water 15 seconds to help loosen and unmold. <br>
                </div>
            </div>
